<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-1844] Subclasses of groovy.lang.Closure can&apos;t be invoked like closures</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1844</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you create a subclass of groovy.lang.Closure and try and invoke it like closure() you get MME for doCall() on the owner of the object. You have to instead do closure.call() which is annoying.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
